Abraham Lincoln to Mason Brayman, 31 March 18541 I write this to inform that the people, (or some of them) ofMcLeanandDeWittcounties, through whose farms theI. C. R. R.passes, are complaining very much that theCo,does not keep it's covenants in regard to making fences–2Anold manfrom DeWitt, was down here the other day to get me to bring a suit on this account;
               but as I had sold myself out to you, I turned him over toStuart, who, I understand, will bring the suit–3 A stitch in time may save nine in this matter–  No decision yet in our tax case; and
               I am not quite easy about it–4
